<TITLE> Stage set for much-trumpeted dialogue </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)  The stage is set for a Thursday start to government dialogue with political parties at the Chief Adviser's Office. The Workers Party of Bangladesh is scheduled to be the first to join the talks with chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed at 10:00am, followed by the dialogue with Bikalpadhara Bangladesh at 4:00pm. Rashed Khan Menon leads the seven-member team of the WPB, and Professor AQM Badruddoza Chowdhury will head the Bikalpadhara team. WPB general secretary Bimal Biswas and politburo members Haider Akbar Khan Rano, Anisur Rahman Mallick, Fazle Hossain Badsha, Hajera Sultana and Quamrul Hasina are on the WPB team. The Bikalpadhara team includes party secretary general Abdul Mannan and other leaders MA Halim, Giasuddin Ahmed Chowdhury, Mahi B Chowdhury, Professor Abdur Rashid and Kartik Thakur. The chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim Wednesday told bdnews24.com that all preparations were complete to hold the dialogue. "The CA will have talks with the Workers Party of Bangladesh for two hours from 10:00am and with the Bikalpadhara Bangladesh from 4:00pm to 6.00pm," Munaim said. Five advisers who had pre-dialogue talks with the parties would be present at the formal talks, he added. Dialogue with the JSD (Inu) has been scheduled for 3:00pm Sunday, and Communist Party of Bangladesh for 10:00am and Liberal Democratic Party for 3:00pm Monday. Political leaders and advisers will brief reporters after every meeting. Against the backdrop of the political parties demanding direct meetings with the chief adviser, five advisers had held pre-dialogue talks starting on April 18. Law adviser AF Hassan Ariff, communications adviser Ghulam Quader, LGRD adviser Anwarul Iqbal and foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman represented the government during the pre-dialogue talks. The advisers first sat in pre-dialogue talks with the Awami League and then with a BNP faction, Jatiya Party and other political parties. Fakhruddin in his address to the nation on May 12 hoped that national unity would achieved on every important issue through the dialogue. bdnews24.com/
